            <li><span class="text-info">Facebook Graph API:</span> Importing content from facebook feeds and timelines into websites.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Twitter API:</span> Display Twitter feeds on a website.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Heroku Platform API:</span> Listing, managing and configuring hundreds of Heroku apps.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Cloudinary:</span> I've used cloudinary to give users of a CMS the ability to crop and size their website photos right in the browser, and to serve responsive images based on screen size.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Amazon S3:</span> Storing static website assets on cloud and hosting basic sites.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Google Maps Platform:</span> Displaying maps on websites and Geocode lookups of street addresses.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">RefineryCMS:</span> I've built several sites using RefineryCMS as a content management system.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Chatmeter:</span> I've worked with Chatmeter's API to automatically push updates to listing data.</li>
            <li><span class="text-info">Etc:</span> I've also worked with many other services and API's for everything from displaying real time pricing and availability information on a site, to application monitoring, to automating SMS and email messages.</li>
          </ul>
